    "engine": "knitr",
    "markdown": "---\nformat:\n  revealjs:\n    title-slide: false\n    theme: multinivel.scss\n    incremental: true \n    slideNumber: true\n    auto-stretch: false\n    transition: fade\n    transition-speed: slow\neditor: source\n---\n\n\n#\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nif (!require(\"pacman\")) install.packages(\"pacman\") # solo la primera vez\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}\n\n```\nLoading required package: pacman\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\npacman::p_load(lme4,\n               kableExtra,\n               haven,\n               car,\n               sjmisc,\n               sjPlot,\n               stargazer,\n               ggplot2, # gráficos\n               dplyr, # manipulacion de datos\n               equatiomatic) # paquetes a cargar\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}\n\n```\nInstalling package into '/home/tomasurzua/R/x86_64-pc-linux-gnu-library/4.3'\n(as 'lib' is unspecified)\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}\n\n```\n\nequatiomatic installed\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nmlm = read_dta(\"http://www.stata-press.com/data/mlmus3/hsb.dta\")\n\nmlm = mlm %>% \n  select(mathach, female,ses,sector,mnses,schoolid) %>%\n  as.data.frame()\n\n\nresults_0 = lmer(mathach ~ 1 + (1 | schoolid), data = mlm)\nresults_1 = lmer(mathach ~ 1 + ses + female + (1 | schoolid), data = mlm)\nresults_2 = lmer(mathach ~ 1 + sector + mnses + (1 | schoolid), data = mlm)\nresults_3 = lmer(mathach ~ 1 + ses + female + sector + mnses + (1 | schoolid), data = mlm)\nresults_4 = lmer(mathach ~ 1 + ses + female + sector + mnses + ses*sector + (1 | schoolid), data = mlm)\n```\n:::\n\n\n\n::: columns\n::: {.column width=\"20%\"}\n\n:::\n\n::: {.column .column-right width=\"80%\"}\n\n# **(titulo del trabajo)**\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n**Autor1, autor2 & autor3**\n\n\n::: {.red2 .medium}\n\n**Análisis de datos multinivel - 2025**\n\n**Departamento de Sociología, Universidad de Chile**\n\n\n\n:::\n\nSantiago, 18 de Junio de 2025\n\n:::\n\n[Github repo](link al repo)\n:::\n\n::: {.notes}\nAquí mis notas\n:::\n\n# Introducción\n\n- [problema, objeto de estudio] Rendimiento en matemáticas decreciente y aumentan brechas por género\n\n- [factores asociados L1] Nivel socioeconómico y género de estudiantes\n  \n- [factores asociados L2] Nivel socioeconómico de la escuela y composición de género de las salas de clases.\n\n## {data-background-color=\"#5f5758\"}\n\n\n::: {.center .middle}\n\n<span style=\"font-size: 250%;\">¿En qué medida el nivel socioeconómico y el género a nivel individual y de escuela afectan el rendimiento en matemática?</span>\n:::\n\n# Hipótesis:\n\nNivel 1:\n\n$H_1$:\n\n$H_2$:\n\nNivel 2\n\n$H_3$:\n\n$H_4$:\n\n# Metodología{data-background-color=\"#5f5758\"}\n\n## Datos\n\n## Variables\n\n(incluir tablas univariados por nivel)\n\n## Métodos\n\n... se estimó el siguiente modelo:\n\n$$\ny_{ij} = \\gamma_{00} + \\gamma_{01} \\text{ses} + \\gamma_{02} \\text{female} + \\gamma_{03} \\text{sector} + \\gamma_{04} \\text{mnses} + u_{0j} + r_{ij}\n$$\n\n# Resultados{data-background-color=\"#5f5758\"}\n\n\n## Descriptivos\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nscatterplot(mlm$mathach ~ mlm$ses, data=mlm, xlab=\"Ses\", ylab=\"Math Score\", main=\"Math on SES\", smooth=FALSE)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](presentacion-template_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-2-1.png){width=672}\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n## Modelos\n\nLos resultados de los modelos de regresión pueden ser presentados en un coefplot\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nplot_model(results_3, \n            title = \"\", #quitar titulo\n            show.values = TRUE, #mostrar valor de efectos\n            dot.size = 3, #tamaño circulos\n            line.size = 1, #tamaño CI\n            value.size = 4, #tamaño valor efectoss\n            spacing = 1, #espacio entre efectos\n            vline.color = \"red\", # linea roja en punto neutro (0)\n            axis.labels = rev(c(\"Ses\",\n                              \"Female\", \n                              \"Sector\", \n                              \"Mean sed\")), #con rev porque automatico los tira en otro orden\n            show.legend = FALSE) + # variables dependientes\n  theme_bw()\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}\n\n```\nWarning: Using `size` aesthetic for lines was deprecated in ggplot2 3.4.0.\nℹ Please use `linewidth` instead.\nℹ The deprecated feature was likely used in the sjPlot package.\n  Please report the issue at <https://github.com/strengejacke/sjPlot/issues>.\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](presentacion-template_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-3-1.png){width=672}\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n## Resultados {.scrollable-x .smaller}\n\no mediante tablas\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\ntab_model(results_0,results_1,results_2,results_3,results_4,\n          show.ci=FALSE,\n          show.icc=FALSE)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n`````{=html}\n<table style=\"border-collapse:collapse; border:none;\">\n<tr>\n<th style=\"border-top: double; text-align:center; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold; padding:0.2cm;  text-align:left; \">&nbsp;</th>\n<th colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-top: double; text-align:center; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold; padding:0.2cm; \">mathach</th>\n<th colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-top: double; text-align:center; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold; padding:0.2cm; \">mathach</th>\n<th colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-top: double; text-align:center; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold; padding:0.2cm; \">mathach</th>\n<th colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-top: double; text-align:center; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold; padding:0.2cm; \">mathach</th>\n<th colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-top: double; text-align:center; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold; padding:0.2cm; \">mathach</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\" text-align:center; border-bottom:1px solid; font-style:italic; font-weight:normal;  text-align:left; \"